Oct 20 2009 	PERFECT - Wouldn't stay anywhere else	Me and my friend stayed at the hotel for 4 nights for a short break in Dubai. We were two females and so wanted a secure place in a good location. In a nutshell the hotel was a perfect base to explore the city.The hotel was a 10-15 min drive from the airport and taxi drivers never had a problem finding the property. Check-in was very smooth and our twin room was ready for us on arrival. Staff were always very polite. The hotel has a rooftop pool and a pool bar with amazing views of the city esp. at night. A gym and sauna room are also located on the rooftop. Our room was a good size (see pix) with a minibar, hair dryer, iron and iron board, kettle and complimentary tea/coffee supplies, LCD tv, coffee table and 2x chairs. Complimentary bottles of water were provided every day and was very helpful and the room was serviced to perfection on a daily basis. The bathroom was of a good size (see pix) and contained the usual amenities. Staff at the concierge desk were extremely helpful. We got most of our local information from them and they also booked our safari tour with just 2 days notice at no extra cost. They sell postage stamps aswell. A free shuttle bus to Dubai mall and Jumeira beach is available thought it has a limited service. The location of the hotel is particularly good for a tourist. There is a metro station (financial centre) 2 mins away and taxis are very easily available. Next door to the hotel is a Nando's and KFC that are open till 2 or 3 am. Down one block is a Subway that is open 24 hrs and further down is a McDonalds and TGI's (5 min walk max). The eatieries come in very handy given that you might be shopping till late. Small grocery type stores are located behind the hotel where you can stock up on water and drinks. I would strongly recommend this hotel to anyone who is planning on visiting Dubai.	
