Mar 10 2009 	Almost Five Star Hotel	Stayed at this hotel for six days during the Sevens Rugby World Cup. The hotel is located on the Sheikh Zayed Road between the Crowne Plaza and Shangri-La. There is much construction going on in front of the hotel along the Sheikh Zayed Road for the subway system that is scheduled to open later in the year and in 2010.The front desk was very accommodating and friendly, and went the extra mile to ensure that the room meet our expectations. The room (2 bedroom suite) was great. Immaculate and well appointed. If we needed anything during our stay, all we needed to do was call down and request it, and our request was to our door within ten minutes. The restaurants were way above average hotel restaurants. The food servers are very professional. This hotel has a pool on the 41st floor along with a sun deck and pool bar. The gym is located on the same floor. All of these facilities were in great shape, very clean, and being used during the time in which we were there. The staff on that floor is very competent and very much try to make your stay worthwhile. The key thing about Dubai is that nothing is really within walking distance or even a short drive. If you want to get to the Gold Souk area, you need to take a 20 minute cab ride. If you want to go to the Mall of the Emirates (ski), it is 20 minutes. If you want to go to the Buddha Bar, it is 30 plus minutes. It will take 40 minutes to get out to Atlantis. The good thing about the hotel though was it was sort of half way; if you were staying near the Raffles, you would have to tack on 15 minutes. The other thing about this hotel was that there were always cabs to be had - the longest we had to wait for a cab was approximately eight minutes and that only occurred once. A word about Dubai, there is less construction going on now than there was even six months ago so traffic is somewhat better. You will see a lot of steel work though with no activity occurring. Prices in the malls are outrageous in comparison to prices in the US - so be warned. A regular polo shirt was $140 plus dollars whereas in the states it would only be $70, and less if you went to an outlet mall. Alcoholic drinks can be found in the hotels but again it is expensive - similar to NYC or Alaska prices and perhaps higher. Bars are ok but the ratio of men to women is at least 5 to 1 (or higher). As far as the beaches go, I would recommend Florida, the Caribbean, California, or Hawaii - much bigger, more activity, more fun. Bottom line - would I recommend this hotel - in a heart beat. It is safe, it is very clean, the staff is unbelievably helpful, the rooms are great. There is also a grocery store two blocks away so you can pick up soft drinks, bread, and the like if you want. The hotel is well worth the money, the location is good, and the staff is wonderful.	
