Feb 27 2009 	Exceeded expectations	Family of three with a 9 y.o. child. Stayed mid February. We split our Dubai trip into two: first four nights at the Four Points SZR for sightseeing and the rest at the Madinat Jumeirah for R&amp;R. This worked well for us. The entire experience with this hotel was fantastic. I emailed them before to confirm my booking as it was done through a UAE-based agent and make a request for a room facing Sheikh Zayed Road – love city lights! – on a higher floor. I also ordered The Entertainer, a discount voucher book for Dubai, and arranged with the hotel to hold it for us. (It was about 40 AED cheaper to buy online and the delivery was free.) They were always quick to respond. My room request was granted and – surprise- we were upgraded to a corner room. We got the room straight away even though we arrived early, around 10:30 am. The check-in was swift, the reception staff friendly and efficient. Service in general was excellent throughout our stay.The room was excellent – spacious, clean, well equipped, with a fabulous view of SZR, skyscrapers and Burj Dubai, the tallest building in the world. The king-sized bed was very large and super comfy, the bathroom spacious, shower pressure very good. It was cleaned well and in the evening the curtains were drawn. Two complimentary water bottles were left in the bathroom every morning. The wrap-around balcony was locked, as mentioned in one of the previous reviews. Although I’d love to go out and enjoy the strip of an evening, it was actually comforting that it was locked as we were with our 9 y.o. We enjoyed nice breakfasts, included, at the Mediterranean restaurant on the mezzanine floor on three occasions. It was quiet but very pleasantly so, with a great décor and superb, genuinely warm service. Although, the buffet choice was not the biggest we have experienced, it was sufficient. The food was good and very fresh. We did not use the rooftop swimming pools due to them being on the windy side but loved the rooftop area. It stayed opened until 10pm, not sure what time the bar was open till but it was closed when we were there just after 8pm. On our last night, we sneaked in our own drinks – bought cheaply in Dubai Duty Free on arrival—and enjoyed lounging on the chairs, taking endless photos of the strip, watching the city lights, the great architecture all around and even fireworks. You can walk in both directions from the Four Points, there are lots of eateries close by. We tried Nando’s and Zariya, a Lebanese place next door with quirky décor and friendly service. Also, a walking distance from the hotel, through an underpass across from the Crowne Plaza, is the Emirates Towers, with an upscale shopping mall and some restaurants that get good reviews in Time Out Dubai (Scarlett’s, Al Nafoorah, etc.) which were all buzzing when we there. I can also recommend the Meat Company, a South African steak house at Souk Al Bahar near the Dubai Mall. Four Points was a perfect base to explore Dubai and do the touristy things. Taxis are constantly cruising by so there is never a wait to get one. Airport is 15 min’ ride away (43.50 AED incl 25 AED airport charge); Bur Dubai (Bastakiya), 15 min and 18 AED, Mall of the Emirates 10 -15 min if no traffic and 26 AED; Dubai Mall, 5 min and 8 AED there/15 AED back (has to do a loop on SZR).We had an enjoyable stay at the Four Points and would highly recommend it.	
