Jan 15 2009	A Beautiful Hotel....	We spent four days at the Four Points on Sheikh Zayed Road in December, and had an amazing experience staying at this hotel.The hotel is lovely, and the hotel staff were very helpful and professional. After arriving in Dubai at 6am from a 15 hour flight from Sydney, we were really impressed when the hotel staff allowed us to check in early and upgraded our room to a preferred room!! Our room was located on the 13th floor with a view to Jumeirah Beach, was extremely clean and with a very comfy bed. The breakfast at the hotel was delicious and with a great range of choices, we enjoyed breakfast at the Mediterranean dining room, also one day tried the full buffet breakfast on the ground floor. I wanted porridge for breakfast, however having asked the staff, this was something they normally do not serve. About 5 minutes later however, our waiter came back to our table with a bowl of porridge he had the chef prepare for me, which was delicious.The hotel is in a good location for visiting Dubai... Being on Sheikh Zayed road, it is not too far to take a taxi to the beach, to Bur Dubai, or to the shopping malls. We found that the biggest expense for us on this trip was the taxi fares, as being the only means of transport we caught taxis quite a few times a day. For those who are after a beach holiday, this hotel is not the best choice as the taxi fares will add up, especially with the Dubai traffic jams.The hotel pool and terrace area is really lovely. The weather was warm however quite windy, so we did not swim in the pool during our stay, but enjoyed the sun on the terrace and the views of Dubai.Another good aspect of the hotel was the staff at the information desk. They went out of their way to help us organise our trip, giving us directions for places we wanted to visit, and travel advice.Dubai is unlike any other city we have visited, and we had a really amazing and memorable holiday here. Overall this hotel made our holiday even more enjoyable, and we would love to come back again...I thoroughly recommend this hotel to couples or families, and the location is a good base to visit Dubai.	
