Jan 4 2009 	Good hotel at great location some minor issues	We stayed at the Four Points Sheraton in Dubai from dec. 25 till jan. 3.The hotel is at a great location. From this spot on Sheikh Zayed road the beach, the creek and most of the malls can be reached easily by taxi.We stayed in a one bedroom executive suite. Nice, large living room, good bedroom, nice flatscreens. The bathroom was a bit disapointing for a suite. Shower/tub combination, very small towels and rather small sizewise. This could use some updating, especially for a &quot;executive suite&quot; one would expect a bit more luxury.Seperate toilet, kitchen with a big refrigerator and a washer and dryer in a small cupboard.We had diner in the restaurant (family room) once, a buffet, and it was good. Plenty of restaurants within a 5 minute walk so it's easy to eat somewhere else if you are not in a hotel-dining mood. Supermarket nearby (Lifco), Starbucks, KFC etc.The hotel has a small pool on the roof, with a great view of Dubai and the Burj Dubai across the street. Nice poolbar with good food. Staff in the hotel was very friendly, we used roomservice once and it was quick and had value for moneyConclusion; not a bad hotel, worth the money but the one-bedroom executive suites (aka apartments) could do with better bathrooms. Tip: when staying here take advantage of the happy hours betweeen 6 and 8 pm in the Beer and Wine Room. 2 drinks for the price of 1 with some free snacks (and aclohol is quite expensive in UAE so this is a good deal).	
