Dec 26 2008 	Good base for Dubai	Just returned from having spent 5 nights in Dubai staying at the four points. It is a very good base for the shoppings malls particularly the Dubai Mall which is going to be the world's biggest mall once completed and 15 minutes away. Once we arrived, we were given a voucher each for a treat which could be a sandwich with a soft drink, or a muffin. The bedroom had lovely views and was cleaned daily.The only meal that we had was breakfast which we chose to include as part of our expedia package. This actually worked out cheaper as it was 95 dhms per day. The buffet had an array of goodies including muffins, croissants, cereals, danish pastries along with hot food as well as Arabic choices.We did have room service and that was good and we didn't have to wait too long!There are a few fast food restaurants walking distance from the hotel and there is actually a Nandos next door!Taxis are always passing the hotel. To give you a rough idea of some of the prices - we paid 22 dhms to the Dubai mall, 38 dhms to the airport. (Obviously this might vary due to traffic).The is a free shuttle to the Jumeriah beach park but this only goes twice a day. If you are planning a beach holiday, I would recommend staying at beach hotel as going to the beach every day would mean additional expenses if you used this hotel as a base. But it is excellent for malls and the variety of excursions that can pick you up from the hotel.	
