Oct 17 2008 	Good location good value but some details could be improved.	I stayed 2 nights at this hotel in mid-October while in Dubai on business. In terms of value-for-money, whether on business or pleasure, this is a very good option in a city where hotel rates can be exorbitant. Furthermore, I received an upgrade to a sea-facing, corner (Preferred) room in recognition of my SPG Platinum status. (I was also offered the option of a smoking Suite, but chose the non-smoking Preferred room instead.)Having said that, there were a few details which were a little rough around the edges. First, the free wi-fi in the lobby causes many guest to linger there, and frankly it's not a very large lobby. There is a small table with 4 chairs in-between the main lobby and elevator banks, and these seats are regularly hoarded by laptop-wielding guests. Not the best impression.Second, I found the service to be friendly but lacking. For example, in one of the F&amp;B outlets, the serving staff would all come over and greet me, but when I actually ordered something it took ages to arrive. So to summarise, this is a well-located, good value hotel to which I would return. However, it does not so far earn an &quot;Excellent&quot; rating in my opinion.	
