Aug 30 2008 	Excellent Hotel Very Good Location My best stay in Dubai yet!	I stayed at Four Points by Sheraton, Sheikh Zayed Road, Dubai for 8 nights from 21 August 2008. This was my fifth visit to Dubai and it was my best stay in Dubai yet!I had read the reviews on trip advisor and contacted the General Manager to enquire about early check in and car parking and I received a very prompt response.Check in time is normally 3pm, but my flight arrived at 5am and I was at the hotel for 6am. The General Manager had written that early check in was subject to availability and I let the reception staff know, they let my family check in at no extra cost and upgraded my rooms to an executive 2 bedroom appartment.In addition to this, they provided a proper baby cot (crib) ie not a travel fold away cot and an extra bed at no extra cost.As I had decided to rent a car for the duration of my stay, car parking was important and the hotel has a significant multistorey car park at the rear of the hotel which was free of charge for hotel guests.Dubai is getting more congested and taxis do not serve certain areas very well, therefore, I rented a car. Alot of travel guides tell you to be very careful when driving in Dubai, but as long as you have your wits about you, its no different from driving in London or Birmingham. Car hire is very reasonable (compared to in Europe) and I would definately recommend it. It gives you the freedom to explore Dubai and beyond.The breakfast buffet was very good, there was a good choice of breads, croissants, muffins, pastries, cheese, yogurts, cereals, fruits, the chef prepares fresh eggs to your choice. There was also a selection of hot buffet items and juices. (Elena was particularly helpful to us)The staff were also very friendly and always had a smile on their faces.The reception area is a little small, but given how big our room was I don't particular mind! Also there is free wireless internet in the lobby area, which a lot of people used. Really nice idea for people on holiday emailing family to keep in touch.The room was immaculate and very large, excellent facilities including room safe, satellite TV. Complimentary water bottles are left in the room daily. Another nice touch is a complimentary treat which the reception staff give you on checking in. This gives a selection of treats (Hot drink and a sweet selection/ Beer &amp; pretzels/ fruit selection etc)The roof top area gives fantastic views of Sheikh Zayed Road and surroundings. The Pool and paddling pool were a great hit with the kids.The surrounding area is very lively with a selection of international cuisine within walking distance. In addition to this there are several small corner shops to get water, soft drinks and snacks etc open until midnight.Photos are just as their website and as other people have posted.Great Hotel, Great Service, Look forward to going back again!	
