Jul 18 2008 	Good hotel	I have recently returned from an 8 night stay at the hotel. I enjoyed my stay here and most of the staff are extremely efficient and hard working. I had only one problem with my room over the stay, the manager was extremely efficient in rectifying this and gave us a free upgrade for the inconvenience.As usual the hotel offers to organise certain trips for you, but I would suggest doing this privately as the hotel charges more than double than the ones you can find by looking in the classified section in the free newspaper which is delivered to your room each morning.The breakfast was really not up to a high standard, I have stayed in 3* Hotels where the breakfast has been far better. The staff at the breakfast are good, though pretty slow in delivering your drinks, especially if you want a tea or a coffee. On a few occasions I had finished my breakfast and forgotten I'd even ordered a drink, ready to leave when it was finally delivered. The woman who brings the bills could also do with a course in customer service.The hotel is in a great location, there are many big brand restaurants within a few minutes walk, and taxi's are so cheap everything in the city is easily accessible.The roof top pool and gym are quite small, but the breeze you get at that height is fantastic in the summer heat.I would recommend this hotel to others and I would consider staying here again myself.	
